# SpeakAble HK · brand and UX rules

You are working on SpeakAble HK with a UX/UI designer. The product is an AI-powered assistant tool for everyday Cantonese speech practice. It uses voice cloning so SEN learners and adults can practise speaking at home, using their own voice as the reference. The team is preparing for a summer 2026 invite-only pilot programme (June–August).

**Full brand kit:** see `@docs/brand-kit.md` — always reference it for design decisions. The summary below covers the laws; the markdown covers the detail.

---

## Project stack (this codebase)

- **Build tool:** Vite
- **Framework:** React 18 + TypeScript (strict mode)
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS (extend `tailwind.config.ts` for brand tokens)
- **Component base:** shadcn/ui (`components.json` is set up; customise primitives via the `cn()` utility in `src/lib/utils.ts`)
- **Backend:** Supabase (auth, database, storage) — relevant for invite codes and pilot user accounts
- **Routing:** React Router (check `package.json` for version)
- **Package manager:** Bun
- **Origin:** Lovable-generated (`.lovable/` folder present)

When generating code:
- Components in `src/components/` (shadcn primitives in `src/components/ui/`)
- Pages/routes in `src/pages/` or `src/routes/` (check existing convention)
- Hooks in `src/hooks/`
- Supabase client in `src/lib/supabase.ts` or similar
- Never assume Next.js features — no `app/` directory, no server components, no `next/font`, no `next/image`
- For fonts, use `@fontsource/*` packages and import in `src/main.tsx`

---

## Two surfaces

| Surface | URL | Mode | Audience |
|---|---|---|---|
| Public site | `speakable.hk` | Logged-out, marketing | Outsiders, prospective schools, NGOs, parents |
| Private app | `speakable.naozumi.[domain]` | Logged-in, web app | Pilot participants, internal testers |

At launch the pilot is **invite-only** (summer 2026). No public self-serve sign-up. Demo bookings only on the public site. Pilot users get a private URL + invite code, validated via Supabase.

If unclear whether a feature belongs on the public site or the private app, ask before writing code.

---

## Audience hierarchy (B2B-first)

Default reader for `speakable.hk` is **Tier 1**, not end-learners.

1. **Tier 1 · Schools, NGOs, hospitals** — they sign contracts. Lead with reach, cost per learner, pilot results.
2. **Tier 2 · Teachers, learning-support staff** — they recommend us. Lead with workflow fit.
3. **Tier 3 · SEN students, adults, families** — they practise. Lead with warmth and PiPi. Lives at `/for-families`.

---

## The vocabulary law (non-negotiable)

This is not a medical product. We are **an assistant tool**, not clinical software. Never use the left column. Always use the right.

| Don't use | Use instead |
|---|---|
| clinical-grade, clinical | everyday, at-home, daily |
| evidence-based, validated | designed for, built for, made for |
| therapy, treatment | practice, exercises, sessions |
| therapist, clinician | teacher, support staff |
| patient, case | learner, user, child |
| communication disorder | speech needs, speaking confidence |
| diagnosis, assessment | progress tracking, attempt history |
| HKSAR-recognised, accredited | made in Hong Kong, for Hong Kong Cantonese |
| platform | assistant tool, web app, practice helper |

If asked to write copy that includes any retired term, refuse it and suggest the replacement. This rule applies even if the user requests the retired term directly.

---

## Mascot · PiPi 皮皮

PiPi is the parrot from the existing logo. Use rules:

- **Appears on:** `/for-families` and inside the web app (practice screens, celebrations, tips)
- **Cameo only on:** the public homepage (small, near the brand mark)
- **Never appears in:** error states, settings pages, professional/institution pages, admin views
- **Never:** sad, scolding, or paired with medical props

