## Color tokens (extend `tailwind.config.ts` with these)

Always use these exact hex values. No improvising.

```ts
// tailwind.config.ts — theme.extend.colors
{
  sky: {
    DEFAULT: '#4FB4E8',
    50: '#EBF6FD',
    100: '#C5E5F7',
    200: '#94D1F0',
    400: '#4FB4E8',
    600: '#1F73A8',
    800: '#0E3A57',
    900: '#072438',
  },
  sunshine: '#FFCB4D',
  coral:    '#FF8A5C',
  mint:     '#6FD4B3',
  ink:      '#1A2541',
  slate:    '#5A6378',
  mist:     '#E2E8F0',
  cloud:    '#F6F8FB',
  success:  '#34B475',
  warning:  '#F5B642',
  error:    '#E85D5D',
}
```

Use as `bg-sky-400`, `text-ink`, `border-mist`, etc.

**Red is for technical errors only.** A mispronunciation uses warning amber with kind copy. Never tell a struggling speaker they are red.

