## Typography

- **Display:** Nunito (weights 400/500 only — never 600 or 700)
- **Body:** Inter (weights 400/500 only)
- **Traditional Chinese:** Noto Sans HK

Install via fontsource: `bun add @fontsource/nunito @fontsource/inter @fontsource-variable/noto-sans-hk` then import in `src/main.tsx`.

Type scale (extend Tailwind's `fontSize`): H1 48px / H2 32px / H3 22px / Body 16px / Small 13px. Line-height 1.6 (English), 1.7 (Chinese).

**Sentence case only.** Never Title Case, never ALL CAPS — including buttons, badges and headings.

---

## UI tokens

```ts
// tailwind.config.ts — theme.extend.borderRadius
{
  sm: '8px',     // inputs
  md: '12px',    // cards
  lg: '16px',    // panels
  pill: '99px',  // buttons, badges
}
```

Buttons are pill-shaped (`rounded-pill`). Cards are 16px radius (`rounded-lg`) with 0.5px Mist border. No drop shadows except subtle elevation (`shadow-[0_1px_2px_rgba(26,37,65,0.06)]`).

Minimum tap target: 44 × 44px. Focus ring: 2px Sky 600.

---

## shadcn/ui guidance

The base shadcn primitives are installed. Customise them — don't fight them:

- **Button:** override default variant in `src/components/ui/button.tsx` to use pill radius, brand colors, sentence case
- **Card:** already close to brand; just verify radius and border match
- **Input:** add Sky 600 focus ring
- **Dialog/Sheet:** brand-friendly already; add Nunito to titles

Never use shadcn's default neutral palette where brand colors should go. The shadcn `--primary` CSS variable should map to Sky.

---

## Accessibility (non-negotiable for our audience)

- WCAG 2.2 AA minimum, AAA target on practice screens
- All semantic colors paired with icons — never color alone
- 44 × 44px tap targets
- `prefers-reduced-motion` respected; no autoplay audio
- Visible 2px focus rings on Sky 600
- Bilingual EN/繁中 by default

---

## When generating copy

- Two languages from day one: English + Traditional Chinese (HK Cantonese vernacular when natural — 嘅, 喺, 啲)
- Tone shifts by surface: institutional pages calm and confident; family pages warm; in-app encouraging and specific
- Specific praise, not generic. "Your tone shape on 媽 was bang on" beats "Good job!"
- No exclamation marks in institutional copy. Limit to one per family page.

---

## When the user says "design a [page/component]"

1. Confirm which surface — public site or web app — before writing code
2. Confirm the audience tier if it's a public site page
3. Reference `@docs/brand-kit.md` if details are needed
4. Output React + TypeScript + Tailwind (using existing shadcn primitives where possible)
5. Include both languages in copy from the start
6. End with a note on which brand-kit sections informed the design, so the designer can audit
